HEADWORD: Blindage
<hw>Blind"age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>blindage</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A cover or protection
for an advanced trench or approach, formed of fascines and earth
supported by a framework.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

